6.3.1 Directional Navigation
Navigation must have a consistent flow to decrease the cognitive load for users and enable integration with various assistive technologies and input methods.

6.3.1-A
Navigation must flow from top-left to bottom-right and start over at top-left when it is finished, without getting stuck. Navigation with only a designated controller or keyboard depends on consistent directional navigation.

6.3.1-B
Users must be provided with two or more ways to locate content. At minimum, this should include menu and search features.
